{
  "texts": [
    "Our hope is to stimulate discussion and thought for what such a framework would require and what it could achieve.",
    "A ML approach to player risk detection typically uses information about gambling patterns and player characteristics from gambling records (behavioral markers) to forecast potential gambling-related problems.",
    "This is similar to the use of biomarkers in medicine, where objectively measured characteristics serve as indicators of disease processes (Biomarkers Definitions Working Group, 2001).",
    "Medicine also uses behavioral markers, for example, in early detection of Alzheimer's disease (Gomar et al., 2011).",
    "ML models can target players according to markers defined by both their gambling patterns and changes in those patterns, using this information to designate differing levels of potential risk."
  ]
}